## 📋 Logging Setup
```python
import logging

logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)

logging.basicConfig(
    level=logging.INFO,
    format='%(asctime)s | %(name)s | %(levelname)s | %(message)s',
    datefmt='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S',
)
```

### Logging Levels
```python
# ✅ Use %-style formatting (lazy evaluation — string built only if level enabled)
logger.debug("Processing row %d: %s", idx, row.to_dict())
logger.info("Loaded %d records from %s", len(df), filepath)
logger.warning("Missing optional column '%s', using default", col_name)
logger.error("Failed to process file %s: %s", filepath, e)
logger.critical("Database connection failed: %s", e)

# ❌ Avoid f-strings in log calls (string always built, even if level is disabled)
logger.debug(f"Processing row {idx}: {row.to_dict()}")  # Wasteful at INFO level
```

