## 🐳 Docker Patterns

### Dockerfile Template (Streamlit Projects)
```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY pyproject.toml .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir .
COPY . .
EXPOSE 8501
CMD ["streamlit", "run", "app/main.py", "--server.port=8501"]
```

### .dockerignore Template
```
.git
.github/
.cursor/
.env
.env.example
*.md
LICENSE
Makefile
tests/
notebooks/
logs/
data/raw/
data/processed/
data/outputs/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
```

### Rules
- Dockerfile lives in project root
- `.dockerignore` keeps image small and secure (no tests, no real data, no secrets)
- Multi-stage builds for production (Stage 2+ optimization)
- `--env-file .env` for API keys at runtime — never bake secrets into images

